│ in the LoopIdiomRecognize pass directly, but in the SCEVExpander when it    │
│ tries to process a SCEV that involves address spaces.                       │
│                                                                             │
│ The root cause is likely that when dealing with pointers in non-zero        │
│ address spaces, ScalarEvolution cannot compute certain expressions,         │
│ resulting in `SCEVCouldNotCompute` objects. However, these objects are      │
│ being passed to the SCEVExpander, which then crashes when trying to use     │
│ them.                                                                       │
